basics.name: Jing Ting Zheng
basics.label: Student
basics.summary: I am studying for a B.S. in Computer Science in the Department of Information and Computer Sciences at the University of Hawaii. I expect to graduate in Spring 2025.

highlights: Conduct user research and product research on gamified digital health to design web applications for digital psychiatric healthcare
Organize monthly volunteer projects and events to increase civic engagement in students
Oversee product development and communication for a civic engagement web application to facilitate community service events and opportunities
Investigated the societal and ethical impacts of artificial intelligence and data processing
Learned about the applications and technical concepts of the different types of machine learning
Vice President, Supporting Women in Information Technology & Computing (SWITCH), 2022-Present

awards.title: Regents Scholarship
awards.summary: Prestigious, full tuition scholarship awarded to 20 freshmen for 4 years of undergraduate study, $4000 yearly stipend, and a $2000 travel stipend.

awards.title: Aspirations in Computing State Winner
awards.awarder: National Center for Women and Information Technology
awards.summary: Recognized for having significantly demonstrated interest and aptitude for computing.
